    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains a 3x3 matrix with one null value, representing categorical coordinates (x,y) paired with quantitative values. Synthetic data follows uniform progression (1-9) with intentional null at midpoint (1,1) to demonstrate missing data handling. The heatmap effectively encodes values through color intensity while using black to emphasize nulls, adhering to Tufte's data-ink principles. The tooltip customization applies Cairo's emphasis on direct labeling - overriding default formatting only for null values maintains visual consistency while providing critical missing data context. Color axis (0-9) matches integer value range, and the simplified tooltip formatter improves clarity compared to default technical displays."
